📖 Project Overview

This project analyzes an airline loyalty program dataset to understand customer behavior, flight patterns, and reward usage. The goal is to extract meaningful insights using SQL queries and help the business improve customer retention and loyalty engagement.

📂 Dataset Description

The dataset contains approximately 39,000 records and includes two main tables:

1. Customers Table
Customer ID
Name
Gender
Country
Enrollment Date
Loyalty Tier
2. Flights / Transactions Table
Flight ID
Customer ID
Flight Date
Distance Traveled
Points Earned
Points Redeemed
🎯 Objectives of the Analysis

The analysis aims to answer the following questions:

Who are the most active loyalty members?
Which customers earn the most points?
What is the average distance traveled per customer?
Which loyalty tier is the most active?
How many points are redeemed vs earned?
What trends exist in customer flight frequency?

